%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stop%20AI%20Slop%2C%20low%20quality%20content%20generated%20by%20Artificial%20Intelligence.%20Traffic%20sign%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5ff2cdce52cb26b83921ee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECompanies%20running%20social%20platforms%20are%20updating%20their%20guidelines%20on%20AI-generated%20content%2C%20especially%20for%20monetized%20accounts.%3Cp%3EMilan%20Surkala%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESocial%20platforms%20are%20updating%20their%20guidelines%20on%20AI-generated%20content.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20has%20been%20a%20point%20of%20tension%20across%20the%20creator%20community%20for%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20how%20social%20platforms%20are%20handling%20AI-generated%20content%20and%20monetization.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20tech%20companies%20race%20to%20weave%20AI%20into%20every%20inch%20of%20their%20products%2C%20they're%20discovering%20there's%20a%20fine%20line%20between%20embracing%20new%20technology%20and%20flooding%20users%20with%20low-quality%2C%20machine-generated%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shifting%20guidelines%20reflect%20a%20broader%20tension%20across%20the%20creator%20economy.%20Not%20long%20ago%2C%20social%20platforms%20competed%20aggressively%20for%20influencers%20with%20creator%20funds%2C%20exclusive%20programs%2C%20and%20monetization%20tools.%20Many%20of%20those%20same%20companies%20are%20now%20investing%20billions%20in%20AI%20products%20and%20infrastructure%2C%20leaving%20some%20creators%20worried%20they're%20becoming%20less%20central%20to%20the%20platforms%20they%20helped%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20major%20social%20platforms%20that%20rely%20on%20creators%2C%20including%20YouTube%20and%20Substack%2C%20are%20dealing%20with%20the%20proliferation%20of%20AI%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EYouTube%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%20this%20photo%20illustration%2C%20a%20Google%20AI%20logo%20is%20seen%20displayed%20on%20a%20smartphone%20with%20a%20Youtube%20logo%20in%20the%20background.%20(Photo%20Illustration%20by%20Avishek%20Das%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5fed0bce52cb26b83921c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EIllustration%20by%20Avishek%20Das%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20is%20sharpening%20its%20stance%20on%20AI-generated%20content%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20update%20from%20the%20company's%20trust%20and%20safety%20team%2C%20on%20July%2020%2C%20YouTube%20said%20it%20wants%20to%20reward%20creators%20who%20use%20AI%20to%20enhance%20original%20storytelling%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20those%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-slop-kids-tiktok-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emass-produce%20generic%20content%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20AI%20personas%20designed%20to%20game%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20YouTube%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20policy%20isn't%20new%20but%20an%20important%20clarification%20of%20YouTube's%20long-standing%20%26quot%3Binauthentic%20content%26quot%3B%20policy%2C%20intended%20to%20reduce%20ambiguity%20for%20content%20creators%20who%20have%20been%20demonetized%20for%20repetitive%2C%20low-effort%2C%20or%20emotionally%20manipulative%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20has%20spent%20years%20pitching%20itself%20to%20advertisers%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube-has-a-big-reason-to-nuke-ai-spam-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efuture%20of%20television%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20a%20surge%20of%20AI-generated%20spam%20threatens%20to%20undermine%20that%20message.%20In%20January%2C%20the%20platform%20removed%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20popular%20channels%20that%20had%20amassed%20millions%20of%20views%20by%20pumping%20out%20AI-generated%20videos%20featuring%20characters%20like%20cats%20and%20Jesus.%20Video%20editing%20platform%20Kapwing%20published%20a%20report%20estimating%20that%2021%25%20of%20YouTube's%20feed%20was%20AI-generated%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETikTok%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22CANADA%20-%202026%2F07%2F04%3A%20In%20this%20photo%20illustration%2C%20the%20TikTok%20(Tik%20Tok)%20logo%20is%20seen%20displayed%20on%20a%20smartphone%20screen%20in%20the%20Apple%20app%20store.%20(Photo%20Illustration%20by%20Thomas%20Fuller%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5fedb2ce52cb26b83921ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EIllustration%20by%20Thomas%20Fuller%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20isn't%20shying%20away%20from%20generative%20AI.%20The%20company%20and%20its%20owner%2C%20ByteDance%2C%20offer%20an%20array%20of%20AI%20tools%20for%20content%20creators%20on%20its%20marquee%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eapp%20and%20video%20editor%20CapCut.%20Creators%20who%20post%20on%20its%20e-commerce%20platform%2C%20TikTok%20Shop%2C%20have%20been%20ramping%20up%20the%20use%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-shop-creators-brands-using-ai-to-replace-human-slop-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20to%20sell%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year.%20Much%20of%20the%20company's%20tech%20is%20built%20around%20ByteDance's%20AI%20video%20model%2C%20Seedance%202.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20TikTok%20is%20taking%20a%20variety%20of%20steps%20to%20keep%20generative%20AI%20under%20control%20across%20its%20ecosystem.%20The%20company%20requires%20creators%20to%20label%20AI-generated%20content%20and%20appends%20an%20invisible%20watermark%20to%20the%20metadata%20of%20some%20videos%20to%20indicate%20they%20are%20artificially%20generated.%20In%20November%2C%20the%20company%20introduced%20the%20ability%20for%20users%20to%20toggle%20the%20amount%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-testing-tool-that-lets-users-limit-ai-content-fyp-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20content%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%C2%A0appears%20in%20their%20feeds.%20In%20July%2C%20the%20company%20said%20it's%20beginning%20to%20test%20%26quot%3Bimproved%20detection%20systems%20to%20target%20accounts%20dedicated%20to%20posting%20AI-generated%20spam%20that%20crowds%20out%20original%20creators.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESubstack%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Substack%20logo%20on%20a%20laptop%20computer%20arranged%20in%20the%20Brooklyn%20borough%20of%20New%20York%2C%20US%2C%20on%20Friday%2C%20March%2031%2C%202023.%20Substack%20Inc.%2C%20the%20online%20host%20of%20writers%20like%20Kareem%20Abdul-Jabbar%20and%20Matt%20Taibbi%2C%20is%20inviting%20contributors%20to%20become%20investors%20as%20the%20newsletter%20publisher%20looks%20to%20continue%20its%20growth%20in%20a%20tough%20market%20for%20fundraising.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5fedf2ce52cb26b83921cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20newsletter%20platform%20announced%20on%20July%2021%20that%20it%20would%20help%20readers%20identify%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubstack-anti-ai-slop-plan-label-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI-generated%20content%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESubstack%20will%20now%20let%20readers%20scan%20content%20to%20estimate%20how%20much%20AI%20may%20have%20been%20used%20in%20its%20writing.%20Substack%20is%20partnering%20with%20Pangram%2C%20an%20AI%20detector%20tool%2C%20to%20power%20its%20AI%20identification%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreators%20on%20Substack%20can%20also%20add%20a%20disclosure%20to%20their%20content%20explaining%20how%20they%20made%20it%2C%20such%20as%20noting%20that%20they%20used%20Claude%20for%20copyediting%2C%20or%20if%20they%20don't%20use%20AI%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20users%20can%20fairly%20easily%20disable%20this%20tool%20for%20their%20Substack%20content%20by%20turning%20off%20AI%20analysis%20in%20their%20publication%20settings.%20Creators%20can%20opt%20out%20of%20Pangram's%20automated%20scanning%2C%20meaning%20readers%20will%20no%20longer%20see%20an%20AI-use%20estimate%20on%20those%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPinterest%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225196%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ound%20Pinterest%20logo%20sign%20mounted%20on%20exterior%20wall%20of%20office%20building%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California%2C%20March%2012%2C%202026.%20(Photo%20by%20Smith%20Collection%2FGado%2FGetty%20Images)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5fee8cce52cb26b83921ce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%20Collection%2FGado%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPinterest%20is%20no%20stranger%20to%20AI%20slop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202025%2C%20the%20platform%20began%20adding%20AI%20labels%20to%20content.%20Pinterest%20lets%20creators%20label%20content%20as%20AI-modified%20or%20-generated%2C%20and%20has%20its%20own%20detection%20systems%20to%20flag%20content%20that%20may%20have%20been%20AI-generated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPinterest%20also%20added%20a%20tool%20that%20lets%20users%20limit%20the%20amount%20of%20AI-generated%20content%20appearing%20in%20their%20feeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20Pinterest's%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpinterest-is-where-gen-z-goes-to-shop-says-ceo-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBill%20Ready%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20Business%20Insider's%20editor%20in%20chief%2C%20Jamie%20Heller%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpinterest-ceo-bill-ready-cannes-lions-ai-shopping-search-genz-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20Cannes%20Lions%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20while%20there%20are%20%26quot%3Bso%20many%20great%20uses%20of%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20there%20is%20also%20a%20%26quot%3Bbit%20of%20a%20counter%20movement%20to%20that%20with%20consumers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20provide%20users%20with%20controls%20to%20decide%20whether%20they%20want%20to%20see%20more%20or%20less%20GenAI%20content%20in%20their%20feed%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Pinterest%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAdditionally%2C%20our%20Community%20Guidelines%20apply%20to%20GenAI%20content%2C%20and%20our%20recommendation%20system%20prioritizes%20high-quality%20content%2C%20regardless%20of%20if%20it's%20human-created%20or%20GenAI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EMeta%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Instagram%20logo%20is%20displayed%20on%20a%20smartphone%20screen%20in%20this%20photo%20illustration%20in%20Brussels%2C%20Belgium%2C%20on%20March%2029%2C%202026.%20Governments%2C%20parents%2C%20and%20regulators%20are%20advocating%20for%20stricter%20safeguards%20to%20protect%20children%20online%20following%20lawsuits%20and%20investigations%20into%20social%20media%20addiction%2C%20exposure%20to%20harmful%20content%2C%20and%20risks%20to%20minors'%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5feef0548c9c486b30ec7d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Raa%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20wants%20users%20to%20create%20and%20engage%20with%20content%20made%20with%20its%20own%20AI%20tools%2C%20so%2C%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20it%20has%20let%20content%20like%20the%20famed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-facebook-ban-ai-slop-images-shrimp-jesus-why-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShrimp%20Jesus%3C%2Fa%3E%20run%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20company%20has%20been%20labeling%20content%20as%20AI-generated%20since%202024.%20Across%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20Threads%2C%20Meta%20adds%20an%20%26quot%3BAI%20info%26quot%3B%20label%20to%20content%20it%20detects%20as%20AI-generated.%20It%20doesn't%20automatically%20do%20the%20same%20for%20content%20that%20was%20modified%20with%20AI%2C%20though.%20Meta%20%26quot%3Bmay%20require%26quot%3B%20its%20AI%20labels%20on%20content%20with%20%26quot%3Bphotorealistic%20video%20or%20realistic-sounding%20audio%20that%20was%20digitally%20created%2C%20modified%20or%20altered%2C%20including%20with%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20company's%20help%20page%20explaining%20its%20AI%20policies.%20People%20can%20also%20voluntarily%20add%20the%20label%20to%20their%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20Meta%20started%20putting%20its%20%26quot%3BAI%20info%26quot%3B%20label%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmetas-ai-ads-push-causes-chaos-for-brands-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvertisements%20that%20use%20AI%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20they're%20created%20by%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMeta's%20own%20tools%20or%20third-party%20editing%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-slop-substack-youtube-tiktok-pinterest-facebook-instagram-threads-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784679960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5ff302ce52cb26b83921ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-slop-substack-youtube-tiktok-pinterest-facebook-instagram-threads-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Platforms%20like%20YouTube%2