actions%20in%20recent%20months%20have%20ranged%20from%20%2429%20billion%20to%20%2442%20billion%2C%20with%20some%20current%20bidders%20even%20attempting%20to%20buy%20shares%20at%20an%20almost%20%2460%20billion%20valuation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeuralink's%20soaring%20secondary-market%20valuation%20reflects%20investors'%20growing%20appetite%20for%20a%20piece%20of%20Elon%20Musk's%20AI%20and%20robotics%20empire.%20Following%20SpaceX's%20blockbuster%20IPO%2C%20private%20investors%20are%20increasingly%20willing%20to%20pay%20steep%20premiums%20for%20access%20to%20Musk's%20remaining%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20Neuralink%20is%20a%20private%20company%2C%20some%20investors%20buy%20shares%20via%20secondary%20markets%2C%20where%20stock%20is%20sold%20by%20employees%20or%20early%20investors.%20These%20valuations%20are%20estimates%20based%20on%20demand%20rather%20than%20continuous%20public-market%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeuralink%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20earned%20a%20reputation%20for%20making%20private%20investors%20money%2C%20partly%20by%20combining%20his%20businesses.%20Investors%20in%20X%20and%20XAI%20were%20able%20to%20eventually%20obtain%20shares%20in%20SpaceX%20via%20those%20acquisitions.%20One%20venture%20investor%20said%20that%20several%20of%20their%20limited%20partners%20have%20been%20asking%20to%20buy%20Neuralink%20shares%20%26quot%3Bat%20any%20price.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20there's%20hardly%20a%20consensus%20on%20where%20Neuralink%20should%20trade%2C%20with%20some%20investors%20balking%20at%20the%20price%20of%20these%20transactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeuralink%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneuralink-elon-musk-microchips-brains-ai-2021-2%23-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20Musk's%20most%20futuristic%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20builds%20brain%20implants%20designed%20to%20help%20people%20with%20paralysis%20control%20computers%20with%20their%20thoughts%2C%20and%20eventually%20restore%20their%20eyesight.%20That%20plan%20is%20still%20early%2C%20with%20the%20chips%20implanted%20in%2021%20trial%20patients%20so%20far%2C%20the%20company%20announced%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeuralink's%20official%20valuation%20and%20whether%20it's%20raising%20a%20new%20funding%20round%20aren't%20clear.%20The%20most%20recent%20publicly%20announced%20investment%20came%20this%20May%2C%20when%20the%20sovereign%20wealth%20fund%20of%20Oman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FOman_OIA%2Fstatus%2F2052029335733973192%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevealed%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20had%20invested%20in%20Neuralink%20at%20an%20undisclosed%20valuation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20wealth%20is%20soaring%20thanks%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-ipo-live-updates-pricing-spcx-stock-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESpaceX's%20IPO%20last%20month.%20%3C%2Fa%3ESpaceX%20is%20currently%20valued%20at%20about%20%241.6%20trillion%20in%20public%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvestors-valuing-elon-musks-neuralink-at-42-billion-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784672508000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5fa85854f9875261777c37%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvestors-valuing-elon-musks-neuralink-at-42-billion-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Neuralink%2C%20the%20brain%20chip%20startup%20owned%20by%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20is%20seeing%20its%20valuation%20soar.%20Investor%20appetite%20for%20Musk's%20companies%20is%20reaching%20new%20highs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22crollet%40insider.com%20(Charles%20Rollet%2CKatie%20Roof)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20Vows%20To%20Help%20Lebanon%20Pursue%20Peace%20With%20Israel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20vowed%20Tuesday%20to%20help%20Lebanon%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%26quot%3B%20as%20its%20president%2C%20Joseph%20Aoun%2C%20sought%20Washington's%20backing%20for%20a%20fragile%20effort%20to%20disarm%20Hezbollah%20and%20forge%20a%20path%20to%20peace%20with%20Israel.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784672114000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-vows-to-help-lebanon-pursue-peace-with-israel-11803570%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20vowed%20Tuesday%20to%20help%20Lebanon%20%26quot%3Ba%20lot%26quot%3B%20as%20its%20president%2C%20Joseph%20Aoun%2C%20sought%20Washington's%20backing%20for%20a%20fragile%20effort%20to%20disarm%20Hezbollah%20and%20forge%20a%20path%20to%20peace%20with%20Israel.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A97%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-vows-to-help-lebanon-pursue-peace-with-israel-11803570%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-vows-to-help-lebanon-pursue-peace-with-israel-11803570%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-vows-to-help-lebanon-pursue-peace-with-israel-11803570%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20Kalshi's%20plan%20to%20attract%20Wall%20Street%20traders%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Inside%20Kalshi's%20plan%20to%20attract%20Wall%20Street%20traders%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2Fz9vRlrZw-.html%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EPrediction%20market%20platform%20Kalshi%20has%20grown%20into%20a%20multi-billion-dollar%20business%20thanks%20to%20retail%20traders%20putting%20money%20on%20everything%20from%20election%20outcomes%20to%20reality%20TV%20winners.%20But%20now%20the%20company%20wants%20institutional%20investors%20to%20use%20the%20platform.%20Why%20the%20push%2C%20and%20will%20it%20work%3F%20BI's%20Dan%20DeFrancesco%20sits%20down%20with%20Kalshi's%20Head%20of%20Institutional%2C%20Andy%20Ross.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-kalshis-plan-to-attract-wall-street-traders-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784669671000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5fdd60548c9c486b30ec14%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-kalshis-plan-to-attract-wall-street-traders-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kalshi's%20Head%20of%20Institutional%2C%20Andy%20Ross%2C%20tells%20Dan%20DeFrancesco%20why%20the%20prediction%20market%20wants%20more%20professional%20investors%20on%20its%20platform.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ddefrancesco%40businessinsider.com%20(Dan%20DeFrancesco)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%223%20lawyers%20react%20to%20Trump's%20new%20limits%20on%20student%20visas%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22lawyer%20composite%20image%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5f76c554f9875261777994%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ETahmina%20Watson%2C%20Loren%20Locke%2C%20Brian%20Hunt%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20has%20finalized%20a%20new%20rule%20that%20limits%20F-1%20student%20visas%20to%204%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20passed%2C%20the%20policy%20would%20ban%20students%20from%20starting%20a%20second%20academic%20program%20at%20an%20equal%20or%20lower%20value.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20risks%20becoming%20less%20attractive%20to%20the%20world's%20brightest%20minds%2C%20one%20lawyer%20told%20BI.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20has%20announced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-student-visa-dhs-f1-change-duration-of-status-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emajor%20changes%20to%20the%20F-1%20student%20visa%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20reshape%20how%20international%20students%20study%20and%20stay%20in%20the%20US.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20rule%20takes%20effect%2C%20F-1%20visas%2C%20which%20have%20historically%20allowed%20students%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20country%20for%20the%20duration%20of%20their%20academic%20program%2C%20would%20instead%20be%20capped%20at%20four%20years.%20The%20grace%20period%20after%20graduation%20would%20also%20be%20cut%20from%2060%20days%20to%2030%20days%2C%20so%20students%20seeking%20to%20regain%20F-1%20status%20would%20have%20to%20either%20apply%20to%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20(DHS)%20or%20leave%20the%20country%20and%20re-enter.%20Students%20would%20also%20no%20longer%20be%20able%20to%20begin%20another%20program%20at%20the%20same%20or%20a%20lower%20academic%20level%20after%20finishing%20their%20current%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DHS%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dhs.gov%2Fnews%2F2026%2F07%2F16%2Ftrump-administration-issues-final-rule-end-foreign-student-visa-abuse%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20the%20changes%20are%20aimed%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20addressing%20national%20security%20concerns%2C%20visa%20fraud%20and%20abuse%2C%20overstays%2C%20and%20the%20growing%20number%20of%20international%20students%20in%20the%20US.%20If%20the%20rule%20clears%20congressional%20review%2C%20it%20will%20take%20effect%20on%20September%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20asked%20three%20immigration%20lawyers%20to%20break%20down%20what%20the%20proposed%20changes%20could%20mean%20in%20practice%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20international%20students%20should%20know.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20words%20have%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225cfa8c69-7309-4ebd-98d9-ea8a7d2f66b1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'My%20advice%20to%20international%20students%20is%20to%20avoid%20non-essential%20international%20travel%20if%20at%20all%20possible'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tahmina%20Watson%20headshot%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a16027cb4fb977f3597fcd3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETahmina%20Watson.%3Cp%3ETahmina%20Watson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETahmina%20Watson%20is%20a%20business%20immigration%20lawyer%20in%20Seattle.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20far%20more%20than%20an%20immigration%20rule%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20an%20economic%20policy.%20By%20fundamentally%20changing%20the%20international%20student%20program%2C%20the%20United%20States%20risks%20becoming%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fforeign-student-enrollment-drops-us-tightens-visas-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eless%20attractive%20destination%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20world's%20brightest%20minds.%20The%20ripple%20effects%20will%20extend%20well%20beyond%20students%2C%20impacting%20universities%2C%20businesses%2C%20innovation%2C%20local%20economies%2C%20and%20America's%20long-term%20global%20competitiveness%20for%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20current%20immigration%20climate%2C%20my%20advice%20to%20international%20students%20is%20to%20avoid%20non-essential%20international%20travel%20if%20at%20all%20possible.%20Even%20students%20who%20have%20maintained%20lawful%20status%20can%20face%20increased%20scrutiny%20at%20U.S.%20ports%20of%20entry%2C%20and%20policies%20continue%20to%20evolve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20eligible%20for%20Optional%20Practical%20Training%20(OPT)%20or%20STEM%20OPT%2C%20apply%20at%20the%20earliest%20opportunity%20rather%20than%20waiting%20until%20the%20last%20minute.%20Filing%20early%20provides%20a%20greater%20buffer%20against%20processing%20delays%20and%20unexpected%20policy%20changes%2C%20helping%20preserve%20your%20ability%20to%20continue%20working%20and%20remain%20in%20status.%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d3e0e73b-209c-4d5e-b01b-92f973df17a3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'A%20one-size-fits-all%20duration%20won't%20fit%20many%20students'%20degree%20programs'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22520%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lorene%20Locke%20headshot%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5fbd7fce52cb26b8391fb5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22520%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELoren%20Locke.%3Cp%3ELoren%20Locke%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ELoren%20Locke%20is%20the%20managing%20attorney%20and%20founder%20of%20Locke%20Immigration%20Law%2C%20an%20Atlanta-based%20boutique%20firm%20specializing%20in%20US%20business%20and%20individual%20immigration.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFewer%20than%20half%20of%20American%20undergraduates%20finish%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20within%20four%20years.%20The%20Department%20of%20Education%20doesn't%20even%20use%20four-year%20completion%20as%20its%20official%20measure%2C%20and%20instead%20reports%20six-year%20rates.%20Many%20engineering%20and%20architecture%20programs%20are%20designed%20to%20run%20five%20years.%20Doctoral%20programs%20and%20medical%20training%20routinely%20last%20longer%20than%20five%20years.%20A%20one-size-fits-all%20duration%20won't%20fit%20many%20students'%20degree%20programs%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20how%20many%20will%20be%20impeded%20from%20completing%20post-graduate%20employment%20that%20international%20students%20have%20long%20been%20eligible%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20lawyer%2C%20it%20worries%20me%20that%20USCIS%20could%20arbitrarily%20deny%20extension%20applications%20or%20take%20so%20long%20that%20the%20student's%20course%20of%20study%20is%20effectively%20ruined%2C%20and%20there%20would%20be%20no%20recourse%20that%20would%20allow%20the%20student%20to%20get%20back%20on%20track.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBarely%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20ago%2C%20DHS%20codified%20a%20deference%20policy%20promising%20consistency%20for%20people%20the%20government%20had%20already%20approved.%20This%20rule%20strips%20that%20protection%20from%20students.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20invites%20students%20from%20around%20the%20world%20to%20pay%20full%20freight%20at%20our%20universities.%20Holding%20over%20them%20the%20very%20real%20and%20increasing%20risk%20that%20they%20will%20walk%20away%20without%20a%20diploma%2C%20despite%20doing%20everything%20right%2C%20really%20damages%20our%20brand%20as%20a%20good%20destination%20for%20international%20students.%20This%20will%20have%20a%20tremendously%20bad%20economic%20impact.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22800ee476-5a82-42ca-9103-a0aec861605a%5C%22%3E'I'd%20imagine%20this%20would%20have%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20students'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brian%20Hunt%20headshot%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5fbd6154f9875261777d40%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrian%20Hunt.%3Cp%3EBrian%20Hunt%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBrian%20Hunt%20is%20a%20counsel%20at%20immigration%20firm%20Fragomen%2C%20Del%20Rey%2C%20Bersen%20%26amp%3B%20Loewy%20LLP%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20student%20'duration%20of%20status'%20rule%20is%20finalizing%20a%20rule%20USCIS%20published%20a%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20and%20it's%20also%20picking%20up%20and%20dusting%20off%20an%20almost%20identical%20proposed%20rule%20published%20in%202020%20under%20Trump%2045.%20The%20rules%20change%20with%20every%20administration%2C%20so%20this%20is%20not%20a%20surprise.%20I'd%20imagine%20this%20would%20have%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20students.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThis%20introduces%20uncertainty%20into%20the%20equation.%20Next%20spring%2C%20a%20cohort%20of%20students%20whose%20F-1s%20are%20expiring%20%E2%80%94%20who%20want%20to%20get%20into%20the%20skilled%20worker%20pipeline%20%E2%80%94%20will%20be%20applying%20for%20F-1%20status%20extensions%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20That's%20when%20we'll%20see%20what%20happens.%20Are%20they%20going%20to%20approve%20them%20all%3F%20Are%20they%20going%20to%20give%20them%20a%20hard%20time%3F%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrankly%2C%20if%20they%20delay%20them%2C%20in%20most%20cases%20they're%20not%20subject%20to%20removal%2C%20but%20they%20also%20can't%20start%20working%20until%20it's%20approved.%20We'll%20see%20what%20happens%20next%20May%3A%20whether%20the%20skilled%20work%20pipeline%20is%20left%20intact%20or%20damaged.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20visa%20changes%20impacting%20your%20education%20or%20career%20plans%3F%20Email%20Charissa%20Cheong%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Accheong%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eccheong%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20Tess%20Martinelli%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Atmartinelli%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Etmartinelli%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F3-lawyers-react-to-trumps-limits-on-f1-student-visas-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784667111000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5f76c554f9875261777994%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F3-lawyers-react-to-trumps-limits-on-f1-student-visas-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22We%20asked%203%20immigration%20lawyers%20to%20break%20down%20what%20international%20students%20should%20know%20about%20F-1%20student%20visa%20changes%20announced%20last%20week.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tmartinelli%40businessinsider.com%20(Tess%20Martinelli%2CDominick%20Reuter%2CCharissa%20Cheong)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A96%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pete%20Hegseth%20Estimates%20Iran%20War%20Has%20Cost%20%2437.5%20Billion%20So%20Far%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22Defense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20said%20Tuesday%20the%20Iran%20war%20has%20cost%20the%20United%20States%20%2437.5%20billion%20so%20far%2C%20up%20from%20a%20previous%20estimate%20of%20nearly%20%2429%20billion%20in%20mid-May.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784667097000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpete-hegseth-estimates-iran-war-has-cost-37-5-billion-11803455%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Defense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20said%20Tuesday%20the%20Iran%20war%20has%20cost%20the%20United%20States%20%2437.5%20billion%20so%20far%2C%20up%20from%20a%20previous%20estimate%20of%20nearly%20%2429%20billion%20in%20mid-May.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A97%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpete-hegseth-estimates-iran-war-has-cost-37-5-billion-11803455%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpete-hegseth-estimates-iran-war-has-cost-37-5-billion-11803455%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpete-hegseth-estimates-iran-war-has-cost-37-5-billion-11803455%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22If%20AI%20wins%2C%20'made%20by%20humans'%20could%20be%20a%20very%20good%20business%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223487%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Topo%20robots%20on%20an%20assembly%20line%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5fd35954f9875261777e65%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222345%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAI%20is%20probably%20inevitable%20%E2%80%94%20which%20means%20we'll%20see%20more%20anti-AI%20products%20from%20companies%20like%20Substack.%3Cp%3ERoger%20Ressmeyer%2FCorbis%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20is%20coming%2C%20and%20you%20can't%20do%20much%20about%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExcept%20that%20sometimes%2C%20you%20may%20be%20able%20to%20buy%20or%20use%20things%20whose%20selling%20point%20is%20that%20they%20are%20AI-free.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThat%20appears%20to%20be%20where%20Substack%20is%20headed.%20Expect%20lots%20of%20other%20examples%20to%20come.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20economy%20is%20increasingly%20hinging%20on%20the%20notion%20that%20AI%20will%20be%20inexorably%20intertwined%20with%20every%20part%20of%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20increasing%3A%20signs%20that%20consumers%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20some%20consumers%20%E2%80%94%20don't%20feel%20great%20about%20that%2C%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20see%20that%20most%20clearly%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-center-protests-ai-trade-markets-sei-be-morgan-stanley-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanti-data%20center%20backlash%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-state-ai-data-center-moratorium-temporary-ban-2026-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epicking%20up%20steam%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Or%20when%20fans%20of%20A24%2C%20the%20hipster-ish%20film%20studio%2C%20heap%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiewire.com%2Fnews%2Fanalysis%2Fa24-ai-backlash-analysis-1235202507%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escorn%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20indie%20for%20daring%20to%20work%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.google%2Finnovation-and-ai%2Fmodels-and-research%2Fgoogle-deepmind%2Fdeepmind-a24-research-partnership%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20DeepMind%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20think%20it's%20just%20as%20telling%20when%20people%20you%20wouldn't%20think%20would%20be%20worried%20about%20AI%20say%20they're%20worried%20about%20AI.%20Or%2C%20at%20least%2C%20that%20they%20understand%20why%20%3Cem%3Eyou're%3C%2Fem%3E%20worried%20about%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20gist%20of%20Tuesday's%20announcement%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fhome%2Fpost%2Fp-207812763%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESubstack%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20newsletter%20tool%2Faspiring%20social%20network%3A%20It%20says%20that%20AI%20slop%20is%20overwhelming%20the%20internet%2C%20and%20it%20wants%20to%20fight%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20that%20effort%20amounts%20to%20giving%20Substack%20users%20access%20to%20a%20tool%20created%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pangram.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPangram%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20AI-detection%20startup.%20Down%20the%20line%2C%20the%20company%20says%2C%20it%20may%20introduce%20other%20features%2C%20like%20the%20ability%20for%20Substack%20readers%20to%20keep%20AI-generated%20content%20out%20of%20their%20feeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESubstack%20CEO%20Chris%20Best%20takes%20pains%20to%20say%20Substack%20isn't%20opposed%20to%20the%20use%20of%20AI%20in%20general%20or%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20Substack%20content%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EWe're%20not%20against%20people%20using%20AI%20to%20assist%20their%20work%2C%20and%20we%20think%20people%20should%20be%20free%20to%20choose%20which%20tools%20they%20use%20to%20express%20themselves.%20Some%20on%20the%20platform%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsamkriss.substack.com%2Fp%2Fif-you-let-ai-do-your-writing-i-will%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehuman-writing%20maximalists%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20others%20are%20publicly%20exploring%20the%20frontier%20of%20using%20AI%20tools%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DuT3EQPVIEb0%26t%3D1064s%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esweating%20the%20details%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20work%20they%20stand%20behind.%20We%20use%20AI%20all%20the%20time%20at%20Substack%20to%20write%20software%2C%20do%20research%2C%20and%20build%20product%20features%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fon.substack.com%2Fp%2Fsubstack-video-clipper-and-production-tools%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclipping%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fon.substack.com%2Fp%2Fintroducing-country-leaderboards%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etranslations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20common%20sense%20tells%20you%20that%20Substack%20wouldn't%20be%20putting%20together%20an%20anti-AI%20plan%20if%20it%20wasn't%20worried%20about%20AI.%20Or%20if%20it%20didn't%20think%20its%20%3Cem%3Eusers%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20worried%20about%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20giveaway%20is%20when%20Best%20uses%20the%20dreaded%20%26quot%3BL%26quot%3B-word%20to%20describe%20what%20might%20happen%20if%20AI%20growth%20isn't%20curtailed%3A%20%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20we%20do%20know%20is%20that%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20wait%20until%20your%20Substack%20app%20turns%20into%20LinkedIn%20before%20we%20start%20to%20learn%20and%20make%20progress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn!%20How%20gross%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20in%20Best's%20mind%2C%20or%20at%20least%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20people%20Best%20imagines%20use%20Substack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExcept%20that%201)%20I've%20seen%20plenty%20of%20crummy%20Substack%20screeds%2C%20and%20sometimes%20I%20see%20a%20really%20insightful%20LinkedIn%20post.%20It's%20a%20wide%20world%20of%20content%20out%20there.%20And%202)%20a%20couple%20months%20ago%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fpulse%2Fkeeping-conversations-real-linkedin-laura-lorenzetti-9821e%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20it%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewas%20trying%20to%20fight%20AI%20slop%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20there's%20a%20pretty%20good%20debate%20to%20be%20had%20about%20much%20of%20this.%20Are%20people%20opposed%20to%20%3Cem%3Eany%3C%2Fem%3E%20use%20of%20AI%20in%20writing%20or%20any%20other%20kind%20of%20communication%3F%20How%20much%20is%20too%20much%3F%20Who%20decides%20how%20much%20of%20it%20I%20get%20to%20see%3F%20And%20honestly%3A%20If%20the%20SVP%20of%20widget%20production%20wants%20to%20use%20ChatGPT%20to%20write%20a%20boring%20post%20about%20widget%20workflow%20automation%2C%20who%20really%20cares%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20don't%20think%20there's%20any%20debate%20that%20lots%20of%20real%20people%20have%20real%20anxiety%20about%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20leaders%20act%20befuddled%20about%20this.%20They%20shouldn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20spent%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20telling%20us%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-economy-jobs-unemployment-citrini-disruption-openai-anthropic-2026-02%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20was%20going%20to%20reorder%20the%20entire%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20very%20likely%20most%20people's%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20its%20progress%20was%20unstoppable.%20During%20that%20same%20time%2C%20many%20of%20them%20explicitly%20linked%20themselves%20to%20Donald%20Trump%20%E2%80%94%20a%20man%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Finteractive%2Ftrump-approval-tracker%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%2C%20many%20people%20do%20not%20like%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20would%20be%20weird%20if%20people%20%3Cem%3Eweren't%3C%2Fem%3E%20freaked%20out%20about%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20do%20agree%20with%20the%20tech%20POV%20that%20AI%20is%20unstoppable.%20Which%20is%20why%20I%20think%20all%20of%20this%20most%20likely%20nets%20out%20with%20a%20labeling%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20world%2C%20the%20average%20person%20will%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20encountering%20AI%2C%20and%20probably%20won't%20know%20or%20think%20much%20about%20it.%20And%20for%20some%20consumers%2C%20and%20some%20brands%2C%20an%20%26quot%3BAI-free%26quot%3B%20label%20will%20be%20a%20selling%20point%2C%20the%20same%20way%20a%20certain%20slice%20of%20our%20population%20pays%20a%20premium%20for%20organic%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20for%20a%20bunch%20of%20us%2C%20it%20may%20be%20something%20we%20care%20about%20in%20differing%20amounts%2C%20in%20different%20times%20and%20contexts.%20I%20truly%20love%20an%20organic%20hot%20dog%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20also%20eat%20and%20buy%20a%20lot%20of%20super-gnarly%20junk%20food%20made%20who-knows-where%20using%20who-knows-what.%20You%20may%20be%20fine%20with%20AI%20in%20your%20LinkedIn%2C%20but%20hate%20it%20in%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.spotify.com%2F2025-09-25%2Fspotify-strengthens-ai-protections%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpotify%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20industry%20may%20be%20right%20that%20AI%20is%20going%20to%20be%20inevitable.%20But%20%26quot%3Binevitable%26quot%3B%20is%20different%20from%20%26quot%3Baccepted.%26quot%3B%20And%20there%20will%20be%20money%20and%20opportunity%20in%20giving%20people%20places%20where%20it%20isn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubstack-anti-ai-slop-plan-label-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1784666505000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a5fd41454f9875261777e74%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubstack-anti-ai-slop-plan-label-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20AI%20is%20everywhere%2C%20offering%20AI-free%20options%20may%20be%20very%20appealing.%20That's%20the%20bet%20Substack%20is%20making.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pkafka%40insider.com%20(Peter%20Kafka)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A96%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Quote%20of%20the%20